<p>I need a <code>for</code> comprehension that invokes <em>N</em> methods that return a <code>Future[Int]</code> and yield only odd numbers. The following code doesn't work because after the first even result the block returns a <code>Failure</code>: </p>  <pre><code>import scala.concurrent.Future import scala.concurrent.ExecutionContext.Implicits.global  def f1 = Future(1) def f2 = Future(2) def f3 = Future(3) def f4 = Future(4)  for {   i1 &lt;- f1 if i1 % 2 != 0   i2 &lt;- f2 if i2 % 2 != 0   i3 &lt;- f3 if i3 % 2 != 0   i4 &lt;- f4 if i4 % 2 != 0 } yield ??? </code></pre>  <p>How do I get the following result?</p>  <pre><code>List[Future(1), Future(3)] </code></pre>